                         it is truth that purifies, and right Catholique ſaith, Act, 15.9. Sanctifie them in thy truth, Ioh. 17.17. And the truth that ſanctifies is not that of Philoſophy and humane demonſtration, but that of ſcripture and divine revelation, this truth purifies, as it is taught and propoſed by holy Church, which is therefore the Pillar and foundation of truth, 1. Tim. 3.17. Whereupon in the Creed after the holy Catholique Church, ſucceeds the communion of Saints, becauſe there is no true ſanctity, ſave in the holy Catholique Church, the beſt in Heretickes and Schiſmatickes is hypocriſie and ſuperſtition.
